<DOC><DOCNO> AP880319-0097 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-03-19-88 1320EST</FILEID><FIRST>r i AM-BritonsDetained     03-19 0202</FIRST><SECOND>AM-Britons Detained,0207</SECOND><HEAD>British TV Crew Detained after Filming Near Arms Factory</HEAD><DATELINE>STOCKHOLM, Sweden (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Swedish police detained a Britishtelevision crew for three hours and seized film they said mightcontain pictures of classified areas at a weapons factory, policesaid Saturday.   The three Britons were detained Friday night after workers sawthem filming outside Sweden's arms manufacturing Bofors' plant atKarlskoga, 180 miles northwest of here.   A police spokesman at Karlskoga, who spoke on condition ofanonymity, said the men worked for Yorkshire Television, anindependent production company. He declined to give their names.   ``We do not suspect that they were spying. They are well-behavedfellows ... and they are allowed to leave the country any time.''   ``But they may have violated a law which forbids filming suchinstallations as an arms factory,'' he said. ``We will know when wehave developed their film.''   The Swedish government has been investigating Bofors Ordinancecompany because it allegedly exported weapons to countries involatile areas, an act forbidden under neutral Sweden's arms exportlaws.   The company, a subsidiary of Nobel Sweden Industries, also hasdrawn attention after allegations of extensive bribing inconnection with a major artillery deal with India.</TEXT></DOC>